Durban - A 32-year-old man is fighting for his life after he was shot twice in the head on Tuesday afternoon. According to Prem Balram, director of Reaction Unit SA, the man was a victim of a suspected robbery. Balram said paramedics found the man collapsed on the road side in Phoenix at approximately 5.29pm. "Paramedics treated him for two gunshot wounds to his head before transporting him to the hospital in a critical condition. The motive for the shooting is subject to investigation however it is alleged that the man was a victim of a robbery." Balram said several witnesses said they had heard gunshots shortly before the victim emerged from a canal and collapsed on the road side, bleeding extensively from his head. KwaZulu-Natal police say they were aware of the shooting and are investigating. No further information was available. POST 